    {
      "id": "20f5230c87de2de86515dacdf03c2ca13b290c10",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-09-14 16:41:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nPer discussion with Mike, the commit comment is misleading, because it isn't ext4 that is changing the i_version at all.  Rather, fsfilt_ext3.c is updating i_version, but ldiskfs is patched to write i_fs_version to disk (which is untouched from the time it is initialized to 1).\n\nBeyond that, the check for last_rcvd < inode_ver is potentially broken and would cause permanent recovery problems under some conditions (e.g. last_rcvd is lost, and transno is reset to 0), so I don't think it should land.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
